Abstraction Abstraction Abstraction Identifying important aspects while ignoring details (separating important concerns) Abstraction permeates software development From natural language descriptions to mathematical models From requirements to code one specification but many realizations From products to process Models are abstractions of reality Abstraction depends on purpose or point of view Previous slide Next slide Back to the first slide View Graphic Version